config INFINIBAND_ROCM_ERNIC
	tristate "AMD ROCm ERNIC - Emulated RDMA NIC Driver"
	depends on PCI && INET
	help
	  This driver provides support for AMD ROCm ERNIC (Emulated RDMA NIC),
	  designed for use with libvfio-user based userspace device emulation.
	  
	  The driver enables RDMA functionality in virtual machines through
	  a userspace server that bridges to host InfiniBand hardware. It
	  includes polling logic to handle asynchronous operations in
	  vfio-user environments.
	  
	  This driver is based on VMware's PVRDMA driver but has been adapted
	  for AMD's ROCm ecosystem and enhanced for vfio-user compatibility.
	  
	  If unsure, say N.
